The paper deals with facial recognition systems and their biases, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the need for subgroup-specific thresholds, which relates to the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper includes a human evaluation, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
